    div.fl.w-100.tc.mt2.ph4.pb2.bg-black-10#dobjobs
      p.f3.tl.mt3.mb1 Buildings with new DOB permit applications filed last month
      p.f6.tl.mt0.mb3.lighttext.lh-copy Construction permit applications show a landlord's intention to do construction and renovations, which can be used to destabilize apartments: for example, Alt 2 permits may represent work that will justify Individual Apartment Improvement rent increases 
        span.no-print (
        a(href='http://www1.nyc.gov/assets/buildings/pdf/pw1_userguide.pdf', target='_blank').no-print more info on permit types, p.5
        span.no-print ). Click a building's 
        a(href='http://a810-bisweb.nyc.gov/bisweb/bsqpm01.jsp', target='_blank').no-print (DOB)
        span.no-print  link for details through the Building Information System
        span . 
